# FundForge - Crowdfunding Platform

## Ground Rules

Before making **any changes** to this project, you MUST first read and understand these three files in full:
1. `TASKS.md` — the project roadmap and current phase
2. `FundForge.md` — the complete requirements specification
3. `.opencoderules` — this file, containing all conventions, rules, and architecture decisions

Only after confirming you understand the relevant sections should you proceed with implementation.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js (JavaScript) - Frontend framework
- BetterAuth - Authentication
- Tailwind CSS - Styling
- Gravity UI Icons - Icon library
- Express.js (JavaScript) - Backend API
- MongoDB - Database (do NOT use Mongoose, use native MongoDB driver)
- Swiper Slider - Carousels/sliders
- Stripe - Payment processing
- imgBB - Image uploading
- Nodemailer - Email notifications

## Project Structure
```
/backend          - Express.js API server
  /config         - DB config, middleware
  /controllers    - Route handlers
  /models         - MongoDB schemas/helpers (no Mongoose)
  /routes         - Express route definitions
  /middleware     - Auth & RBAC middleware
  /utils          - Email, notifications helpers
/frontend         - Next.js app
  /src
