## Core Data Models (MongoDB Collections)

### users
```
{ name, email, password, photoUrl, role: "supporter"|"creator"|"admin", credits: Number, createdAt }
```
- Supporter gets 50 credits on registration, Creator gets 20.

### campaigns
```
{ title, story, category, fundingGoal, minimumContribution, deadline, rewardInfo, imageUrl, creatorEmail, creatorName, amountRaised: 0, status: "pending"|"approved"|"rejected", createdAt }
```

### contributions
```
{ campaignId, campaignTitle, contributionAmount, supporterEmail, supporterName, creatorName, creatorEmail, date, status: "pending"|"approved"|"rejected" }
```

### withdrawals
```
{ creatorEmail, creatorName, withdrawalCredit, withdrawalAmount, paymentSystem, accountNumber, withdrawDate, status: "pending"|"approved" }
```

### payments
```
{ userEmail, userName, credits, amount, stripePaymentId, date }
```

### notifications
```
{ message: String, toEmail: String, actionRoute: String, time: Date }
```

### reports
```
{ supporterEmail, supporterName, campaignId, campaignTitle, reason, date }
```

## Routing / Pages

### Public Routes (Basic Layout)
- `/` - Home page (Hero slider, Top 6 funded campaigns, Testimonials, 3 custom sections)
- `/login` - Login (email/password + Google OAuth)
- `/register` - Registration (name, email, photoUrl, password, role dropdown)

### Dashboard Routes (Dashboard Layout)
**Supporter:** `/dashboard/supporter/home`, `/dashboard/supporter/explore`, `/dashboard/supporter/campaign/[id]`, `/dashboard/supporter/contributions`, `/dashboard/supporter/purchase-credits`, `/dashboard/supporter/payment-history`

**Creator:** `/dashboard/creator/home`, `/dashboard/creator/add-campaign`, `/dashboard/creator/my-campaigns`, `/dashboard/creator/withdrawals`, `/dashboard/creator/payment-history`

**Admin:** `/dashboard/admin/home`, `/dashboard/admin/manage-users`, `/dashboard/admin/manage-campaigns`, `/dashboard/admin/withdrawal-requests`, `/dashboard/admin/reports`

## Navbar Rules
- **Not logged in:** Logo, Explore Campaigns, Login, Register, "Join as Developer" (links to GitHub repo)
- **Logged in:** Logo (links to home), Dashboard, Available Credits, User Profile + Logout, "Join as Developer"

## Business Logic
- 10 credits = $1 (purchase rate)
- 20 credits = $1 (withdrawal rate for creators)
- Minimum 200 credits to withdraw
- New campaigns saved as "pending", visible only after admin approval
- Approving contribution: add amount to campaign's amountRaised, set status "approved"
- Rejecting contribution: set status "rejected", refund credits to supporter
- Deleting a campaign: refund all approved supporters
- Admin approves withdrawal: decrease creator's raised credits by withdrawal amount

## Feature Implementation Rules

### Authentication (BetterAuth)
- Registration: form fields + Google OAuth
- Login: email/password + Google Sign-In
- Input validation: email format, password strength, existing email check
- Redirect to dashboard after login/registration
- No credit re-issuance (only once on registration)

### Home Page
- Hero section with Swiper slider (3 banners) or background video
- Top 6 funded campaigns section (by amountRaised), show cover image, title, total raised
- Testimonial section with Swiper (static data, photo + name + quote)
- Minimum 3 extra custom sections (e.g. "How It Works", "Explore by Category", "Platform Impact in Numbers")
- Home page must include animations

### Creator Dashboard
- **Home:** total campaigns, active campaigns (deadline not passed), total raised
- **Contributions to Review:** table of pending contributions with Approve/Reject buttons + View Contribution modal
- **Add New Campaign:** form with title, story, category, fundingGoal, minimumContribution, deadline, rewardInfo, imageUrl (imgBB upload)
- **My Campaigns:** table sorted by deadline descending, Update (title/story/rewardInfo) and Delete (refund supporters + delete campaign) buttons
- **Withdrawals:** show earnings (credits + dollar equivalent), withdrawal form (creditsToWithdraw, auto-calc $, Stripe dropdown, account number), Withdraw button or "Insufficient credit" text
- **Payment History:** table of all withdrawal payments

### Supporter Dashboard
- **Home:** total contributions count, pending count, approved total amount
- **Approved Contributions:** table of approved contributions (campaignTitle, amount, creatorName, status)
- **Explore Campaigns:** card grid of approved + not-expired campaigns (title, creator, deadline, goal, raised, View Details)
- **Campaign Details:** full campaign info + contribution form (amount input → saves with status "pending")
- **My Contributions:** table of all user contributions (paginated), highlight status
- **Purchase Credits:** Stripe cards (100cr/$10, 300cr/$25, 800cr/$60, 1500cr/$110), on success save payment + increase credits
- **Payment History:** table of all payments

### Admin Dashboard
- **Home:** total supporters, total creators, total available credits, total payments processed
- **Manage Users:** table (name, email, photo, role, credits) + Remove + Update Role dropdown
- **Manage Campaigns:** table + Delete Campaign button
- **Withdrawal Requests:** table of pending withdrawals + Payment Success button (approve + decrease creator credits)
- **Reports:** table (reporter, campaignTitle, reason, date) + Suspend/Delete buttons

### Notifications
- Creator approves/rejects contribution → notify supporter
- Admin approves withdrawal → notify creator
- Admin approves/rejects campaign → notify creator
- Supporter creates contribution → notify creator
- Store in notifications collection with { message, toEmail, actionRoute, time }
- Notification icon shows matching notifications sorted descending
- Floating popup, click away to dismiss

### Image Upload (imgBB)
- On registration (profile picture)
- On Add New Campaign (campaign image)

### Email Notifications (Nodemailer)
- Campaign approval/rejection
- Contribution confirmation
- Withdrawal processing

### Search & Filter
- Campaign search/filter by category, deadline, fundingGoal, status
- Use MongoDB aggregation pipeline on server side

### Report System
- Supporters can report suspicious campaigns
- Admin views reports with reporter info, campaign, reason, date
- Admin can suspend or delete reported campaigns

### Authorization
- RBAC middleware: protect routes by role (supporter, creator, admin)
- Each dashboard route accessible only by its role
- API endpoints verify user role from token/session

## Code Conventions
- JavaScript only (no TypeScript)
- No Mongoose — use native `mongodb` driver (client.connect, db.collection, etc.)
- Use ES modules or CommonJS consistently
- Tailwind CSS utility classes for styling
- Gravity UI Icons for icons
- Server-side logic in Express.js backend
- Client-side in Next.js (App Router)
- Component-based React architecture
- Reusable layout components (BasicLayout, DashboardLayout)
